This is a course which includes auditory study combined with web-based support. Seminars and practical training will take place simultaneously with web-based lectures. There are supplementary electronic lecture materials for each subject covered in the course and it is possible to use additional web-based sources to expand knowledge. Individual working through the sources, including literature, is followed by a seminar or practical training where the students can improve his knowledge and put into practice. Throughout the cource the students will learn to understand the possibilities of caries development, individual and professional tools and methods for prevention of oral-and dental diseases.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to teach prophylactic methods of oral diseases.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who have passed the course must  have theoretical and practical knowledge how to prevent oral- and dental diseases and how to implement it into practice. They must know how to counsel patients about the issues of prevention of dental diseases.
